article_title: Insurers signal Obamacare rate hikes, but feds say don’t believe it
article_text:
Financial losses have led health insurers to leave ACA exchanges

Industry signals suggest big rate hikes for 2017 Obamacare plans

Obama administration says subsidies lower costs for many consumers

article_metadata.news-keywords: Obamacare, Affordable Care Act, Health Insurance Marketplace, health insurance, uninsured, premium tax credits, premiums, healthcare, Florida, Miami, Miami-Dade
article_metadata.description: As the health insurance industry signals significant premium hikes for Obamacare plans in 2017, federal health officials say consumers’ actual costs will be lowered by government subsidies, shopping and rate regulation.
